15:33.901 --> 15:36.005
That's the only way the plant would not change, right?

15:36.285 --> 15:37.307
Otherwise, it'll keep growing.

15:37.347 --> 15:39.190
It might get bigger and smaller, right?

15:39.751 --> 15:46.963
It might get leaves that fall off and grow again or whatever, but it's constantly growing and changing.

15:46.983 --> 15:48.786
So for the Christian, it's the same thing.

15:49.147 --> 15:55.858
If you say, I want to be a growing Christian by definition, you have to look at your life and say, how can I change?

15:56.290 --> 16:07.487
If you are a Christian and you say, my Christian walk has not changed at all over these past whatever years, I do exactly the same thing that I've been doing for years and years and years.

16:08.028 --> 16:08.870
I will tell you this.

16:08.910 --> 16:15.320
It's very likely that you are not growing as a Christian, that you are static as a Christian.

16:15.340 --> 16:20.247
Now, once again, once again, change is not always indicative of growth, right?

16:20.267 --> 16:21.970
You can always have change for the worse.

16:22.050 --> 16:22.371
Right?

16:22.691 --> 16:26.478
You could say, I go to church now and then now I do not go to church anymore, right?

16:26.738 --> 16:28.481
That would be a change for the worse, right?

16:29.203 --> 16:32.589
And there's some people that believe in radical change.

16:33.009 --> 16:36.996
And same thing, I'll say the same thing as I said about weight loss and they say about change in Christians.

16:37.357 --> 16:43.568
A lot of times when we see radical change that's often a sign of Christian immaturity, right?

16:43.648 --> 16:44.850
The people that say, oh,

16:44.994 --> 16:45.935
I don't read the Bible.

16:46.255 --> 16:47.977
Now, all of a sudden, I'm on fire.

16:48.117 --> 16:53.502
I'm going to read 20 Bible chapters a day, and I'm going to read and read and read nonstop.

16:54.183 --> 16:56.485
Those are the same people that might get burned out, right?

16:56.565 --> 17:02.551
To say that, oh, now I've done this, and I'm sick of reading 20 chapters a day, and I go down to reading zero, right?

17:02.911 --> 17:06.294
Just like the weight loss people, you don't do it all at once, and you don't do it crazily.

17:06.915 --> 17:09.497
It's about an evolution, growing and changing.

17:09.837 --> 17:14.642
The same way a plant doesn't grow from a seed into a huge tree in one day,

17:15.074 --> 17:18.379
